@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy and Usage Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
<p><strong>Last Updated: August 28, 2025</strong></p>
<hr />

<p>
    This policy outlines the data, privacy, and usage principles for the Corporate Knowledge Base platform ("the Platform"), developed by <strong>[Company Name]</strong> and accessible only through the company's internal local network (intranet).
</p>

<h3>1. Data We Collect</h3>
<p>During your use of the Platform, we collect and store the following types of data:</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Account Information:</strong> Identity information you provide during registration or profile updates, such as your Name, Surname, Corporate Email Address, and Profile Picture.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>User-Generated Content:</strong> Blog Posts, Technical Documents, and Announcements you add to the Platform. All content you create is associated with your profile as author information and is considered company property.
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>2. Purpose of Data Use</h3>
<p>The collected data is used for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
    <li>To identify the authors of content on the Platform and to track the source of information.</li>
    <li>To ensure application security and prevent unauthorized access.</li>
    <li>To contact you for internal communication when necessary (e.g., to verify the accuracy of content).</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Data Sharing and Responsibility</h3>
<p>
    All data on this platform is strictly for <strong>internal company use</strong>. Exporting, copying, or sharing information from the Platform (including posts, documents, user information, etc.) with external parties or unauthorized individuals is strictly prohibited and subject to company disciplinary regulations.
</p>

<h3>4. User Rights and Content Management</h3>
<p>As a user of the Platform, you have the following rights:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> You can update your personal information (Name, Surname, Profile Picture, etc.) through the "Account Settings" page.</li>
    <li><strong>Content Management:</strong> The right to edit and delete the content you have created belongs to you or the system administrators, depending on your role.</li>
</ul>

<h3>5. Policy Changes</h3>
<p>
    Significant changes to this policy will be communicated to all users via an announcement on the Platform.
</p>